init_text:
A woman has been dating guy after guy, but it never seems to work out. She’s unaware that she’s actually been dating the same guy over and over; a shapeshifter who’s fallen for her, and is certain he’s going to get it right this time.

One day,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: she’s walking down the street and sees a man she’s never seen before.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She’s not sure why she’s so interested, but she feels like she’s seen him before.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She’s never been to this part of town before, but she feels like she’s been here before.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She looks up and sees him looking at her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She looks down at her phone and pretends to send another text.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She looks up again, and he’s gone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She gasps and drops her phone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: “I’m sorry,” he says, bending down to pick it up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She feels a jolt of electricity.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: she says, pulling her hand back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She felt like she was going to melt.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She smiled at him, and he smiled back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He smiled again, and she felt her knees go weak.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She looked at him, her heart pounding.
